comment: LATR shows that Gobert (UTA) legally contests Jackson's (DET) driving layup attempt.
Morris (DET) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Hayward's (UTA) drive and shot attempt.
Gobert (UTA) dislodges Baynes (DET) affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.

After communicating with the Replay Center, there was conclusive video evidence that showed that Detroit touched the ball prior to it going OOB. The ruling on the court of a jump ball was overturned and Utah was awarded possession.
Tolliver (DET) and Favors (UTA) make incidental foot to foot contact that causes both players to stumble.
Gobert (UTA) and Morris (DET) make incidental leg to leg contact after Gobert's pass.
Gobert (UTA) sets the screen on Caldwell-Pope (DET) without giving him room to avoid the contact and affecting his ability to defend the jump shot attempt.
Hayward (UTA) commits a take foul on Jackson (DET).
Johnson (UTA) commits a take foul on Jackson (DET).
Morris (DET) makes incidental contact with Hayward (UTA) that does not affect his FOM away from the ball.
Hayward (UTA) maintains his pivot foot on the pump fake.
